abstract.text: A byte buffer in memory.

inlineContent.text: value type allows simple byte buffers to take on the behavior of Foundation objects. You can create empty or pre-populated buffers from a variety of sources and later add or remove bytes. You can filter and sort the content, or compare against other buffers. You can manipulate subranges of bytes and iterate over some or all of them.
. You can use these interchangeably in code that interacts with Objective-C APIs.
